## 1.4 One-Line Pitch
`A playful tabletop pinball machine built from scratch, driven by an ESP32 microcontroller and servo motors.`

## 1.5 Expanded Project Idea
In 1â€“2 paragraphs, explain:
- what your project is,
- what kind of playful experience it creates,
- what makes it fun, curious, engaging, strange, satisfying, competitive, or delightful,
- what technologies are involved.

**Response:**  
Our project is a miniature pinball machine built as a self-contained tabletop experience. The outer enclosure is laser cut MDF, the interior ramps and guides are cardboard, and the ball is a small plastic ball. Two micro servo motors drive the flipper arms, controlled by an ESP32 microcontroller running MicroPython. Players interact with two roller lever switches â€” one per flipper â€” powered through a breadboard power supply.
What makes it fun is how immediate it feels. The lever switches are light to press, the servos snap fast, and the whole thing runs on pure physical reaction â€” no screen, no app, no instructions needed. The game is simple: keep the ball alive as long as you can. That simplicity is exactly what makes it competitive â€” every round is short, every drain stings a little, and the next attempt starts immediately.
